<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 3:23AM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF CENTRAL SIOUX,
SOUTHEASTERN MORTON AND CENTRAL GRANT COUNTIES THROUGH 400 AM CDT/300
AM MDT/...
At 323 AM CDT/223 AM MDT/, a strong thunderstorm was located 8 miles
southeast of Carson, or 18 miles east of Elgin, moving east at 35
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Shields.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
